# Indian Web 3.0 Startups

India has a rapidly growing Web3 ecosystem with startups working in blockchain infrastructure, cryptocurrency exchanges, enterprise blockchain, and Web3 development services.

---

## Major Indian Web3 Startups

| Startup Name | Year Founded | Founder(s) | About | Website |
|-------------|-------------|-----------|-------|---------|
| Polygon | 2017 | Jaynti Kanani, Sandeep Nailwal, Anurag Arjun | Builds Layer-2 scaling solutions to make Ethereum faster, cheaper, and more scalable | https://polygon.technology |
| CoinDCX | 2018 | Sumit Gupta, Neeraj Khandelwal | Indian cryptocurrency exchange enabling trading, investing, and Web3 ecosystem access | https://coindcx.com |
| WazirX | 2017 | Nischal Shetty, Sameer Mhatre, Siddharth Menon | One of India’s leading cryptocurrency exchanges supporting digital asset trading | https://wazirx.com |
| Biconomy | 2019 | Ahmed Al-Balaghi, Sachin Tomar, Aniket Jindal | Provides infrastructure tools that simplify Web3 transactions and gas fees | https://www.biconomy.io |
| KrypC | 2016 | Karthik Balasubramanian, Ravi Jagannathan | Develops enterprise blockchain solutions for governments and corporations | https://krypc.com |
| Mesha | 2019 | Tahem Veer Verma | Builds Web3-based financial tools for payments, treasury, and stablecoins | https://www.mesha.club |
| SoluLab | 2014 | Chintan Thakkar, Rajat Lala | Offers end-to-end blockchain and Web3 application development services | https://www.solulab.com |
| QuillHash Technologies | 2018 | Preetam Rao, Rajat Gahlot | Focuses on blockchain security, smart contract audits, and Web3 testing | https://quillhash.com |

---

## Tamil Nadu–Specific Web3 and Blockchain Companies and Communities

Tamil Nadu plays an important role in India’s Web3 ecosystem through startups and developer communities.

| Company / Community | Year Started | Founder(s) | About | Website / Source |
|--------------------|-------------|-----------|-------|------------------|
| Web3Chennai | 2022 | Supported by Bharat Web3 Association | Chennai-based Web3 community promoting education, meetups, and developer networking | https://bwaind.in/compendium/web3chennai/ |
| KrypC (Chennai Operations) | 2016 | Karthik Balasubramanian, Ravi Jagannathan | Enterprise blockchain firm with a strong presence in Tamil Nadu | https://krypc.com |
| Web3 Builders Coimbatore (Community) | — | Community-led | Conducts Web3 meetups, workshops, and hackathons in Coimbatore | https://lu.ma |

---

## One-Line Summary

India’s Web3 ecosystem includes globally recognized startups like Polygon and CoinDCX, while Tamil Nadu supports blockchain growth through firms like KrypC and communities such as Web3Chennai.
